cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DS 

The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to identify context-dependent sentences from corpora. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves rule-based algorithms and empirical evaluations, which are common in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with information retrieval and data structures, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
